+## CSRF Contract
+
+- `GET /csrf-token` is the only auth endpoint that is exempt from CSRF validation.
+- Anonymous state-changing endpoints (`POST /register`, `POST /login`) require the `anon_csrf` cookie and the same value in `X-CSRF-TOKEN`.
+- Authenticated access-token endpoints require JWT cookies, `csrf_access_token`, and the same value in `X-CSRF-TOKEN`.
+- `POST /refresh` requires the refresh token cookie, `csrf_refresh_token`, and the same value in `X-CSRF-TOKEN`.
+- Missing CSRF header/cookie pairs return `401` with `detail: "Missing CSRF token"`.
+- CSRF header/cookie mismatches return `401` with `detail: "CSRF token mismatch"`.
+- Missing, malformed, expired, or wrong-type JWT cookies still return `401` with `detail: "Invalid or expired token"`.
 
